invasive surveillance and online labour - emerged in the late 20th century. Exploring everything from the influences on Falk's iconic acting style to the show's depiction of Los Angeles, Martin-Jones illuminates how our attention is channelled, via technologies like television and computers, to influence how we perform, learn, police and locate ourselves in today's world. Columbo emerged alongside shows like Kojak and The Rockford Files, but re-viewing the series today reveals how contemporary television hits - from Elementary to The Purge - continue to shape how and why we pay attention 24/7.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2022) 0aAttention. 0aTelevision broadcastingxSocial aspects. 0aTelevisionxPsychological aspects. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Acting & Auditioning.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2021z9783110753790oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311078039040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474479813zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474479813zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474479813/original  a978-3-11-075400-1 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075403-2 EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-078039-0 Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook